    "en": {
      "title": "Environment Minister to Saudi Arabia as the special representative of the President",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "As a special representative of President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa, Environment Minister Nasir Ahmed is scheduled to leave for Saudi Arabia today (02). He is scheduled to visit Saudi Arabia until the 5th.",
        "Abdullah A.A., Officer-in-Charge of the Embassy of Saudi Arabia in Sri Lanka. Mr. Orkobi, Minister of Foreign Affairs Prof. G.L. These facts were revealed when Mr. Peiris met.",
        "In this meeting, he explained the current economic situation including the fuel crisis in Sri Lanka and the negative impact it has on all sectors of Sri Lanka.",
        "The Minister also insists that it is an extremely urgent matter to provide ways for energy cooperation with the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.",
        "Also, Environment Minister Naseer Ahmed asked the officer in charge to provide facilities for his ongoing visit to Saudi Arabia.",
        "Abdullah A.A., the officer in charge of the Saudi Embassy, \u200b\u200bemphasized on the importance of the bilateral relationship between Sri Lanka and Saudi Arabia. Mr. Orkobi assured Sri Lanka of all possible support in this regard."
      ],
